Epic follow-up to the immortal Hook Champ.  Includes everything that made HC so great (slick controls, smooth gameplay, replayability galore, absurdist humor, hats) while improving on the graphics, sound, sense of speed, and variety of levels.  Also, there are explorin' secrets to find.  And gnomes.

The Avalanche! and Eruption! modes, which are potentially endless and randomly generated, would be enough to justify getting this game.  The fact that there are a bunch of HC-style levels to explore makes the awesomeness factor of Super QuickHook go to 11.

Update:

The new Eruption! mode + new characters + new hats and hooks = the best game gets even better.

Writing this review because I just downloaded Mage Gauntlet. 
Hoping it will unseat SuperQuickHook as my favorite iOS game - going back to 2008. 

I've beaten this game at least 4 times, and I will probably play through it again. Every couple months I'll fire it up again. 
Executed very well, the Hook and swing mechanism is ridiculously fun especially on a touch screen. It has that "just-works" quality to it. 
It has the spirit of a Genesis game, but unlike many designers who attempt that type of look, the control implementation feels so natural. Levels are challenging and exquisitely crafted. 

I don't write reviews. But I've loved everything Rocketcat has put out so far - felt like I owed it to them. This is a must-own. 500 stars.

I've played all 3 hook games, and this one is the best. I'm glad I played the other two first because they are great games, but this one is slick, has great control, tons of achievements, and a bunch of unique levels, all with secrets to be found.

I'd recommend the others first if you plan on buying all 3. If you're only interested in the best, this is the one to get.
